1
00:00:02,887 --> 00:00:07,899
ظآزDo you know, our fingertips
are bound by one stringظآز

2
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:12,499
ظآزTied to an attachment
that blooms only to fadeظآز

3
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,999
ظآزBy your side onceظآز

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,074
ظآزI laughed with the world
wild and freeظآز

5
00:00:17,075 --> 00:00:21,049
ظآزYet now there's no one
to carry the story onظآز

6
00:00:21,050 --> 00:00:25,970
ظآزDo you know you are the one string
woven through my fateظآز

7
00:00:25,987 --> 00:00:30,699
ظآزCoiled through the years,
where longing sharpens into pain's lineظآز

8
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:35,261
ظآزIf love is meant to fall
more wretched the fiercer its flightظآز

9
00:00:35,262 --> 00:00:40,445
ظآزYet I still came to answer your callظآز

10
00:00:40,725 --> 00:00:43,086
=Shall We Dance=

11
00:00:43,087 --> 00:00:46,182
=Episode 4=

12
00:00:47,340 --> 00:00:48,259
Your Majesty.

13
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:50,180
Why did you end up
sleeping on the floor?

14
00:00:56,060 --> 00:00:56,859
Get up now.

15
00:00:56,860 --> 00:00:58,140
You will catch a chill.

16
00:00:59,740 --> 00:01:00,860
Xiao Man.

17
00:01:01,260 --> 00:01:02,699
You may return for now.

18
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:04,860
I will change by myself today.

19
00:01:09,260 --> 00:01:10,700
I will leave.

20
00:01:24,300 --> 00:01:25,780
(So it was a dream.)

21
00:01:26,580 --> 00:01:27,259
Your Majesty.

22
00:01:27,260 --> 00:01:28,660
Your Highness.

23
00:01:28,740 --> 00:01:31,699
Regarding the pacification of the Southern Sea,
our army has won a decisive victory.

24
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,380
It can now be said that...

25
00:01:37,260 --> 00:01:38,260
Your Majesty.

26
00:01:41,590 --> 00:01:43,179
I wonder
what Your Majesty thinks of this.

27
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:44,459
Why would I have such a strange dream?

28
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:45,300
Your Majesty.

29
00:01:46,020 --> 00:01:47,140
Your Majesty.

30
00:01:47,260 --> 00:01:48,420
Your Majesty.

31
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:49,859
Ah?

32
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:50,980
Ah...

33
00:01:51,140 --> 00:01:53,219
With the Grand Princess
handling it this way,

34
00:01:53,220 --> 00:01:54,259
I find it inappropriate.

35
00:01:54,260 --> 00:01:55,179
Enough.

36
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:57,460
I am tired today as well.

37
00:01:58,460 --> 00:02:00,100
That will be all.

38
00:02:00,340 --> 00:02:01,379
Thank you, Aunt.

39
00:02:01,380 --> 00:02:02,500
Then...

40
00:02:03,580 --> 00:02:05,740
I will go play cuju.

41
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:10,859
If there is nothing else,

42
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:12,100
you may all disperse.

43
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:16,859
Xiao Man.

44
00:02:16,860 --> 00:02:17,619
Let us go.

45
00:02:17,620 --> 00:02:18,620
Yes.

46
00:02:18,860 --> 00:02:21,340
We respectfully see Your Majesty off.

47
00:02:28,780 --> 00:02:29,900
What are you doing?

48
00:02:38,780 --> 00:02:39,899
Your Majesty.

49
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:42,579
That was the cup I was just using.

50
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:43,819
I know.

51
00:02:43,820 --> 00:02:45,260
I do not mind.

52
00:02:56,260 --> 00:02:57,540
But you mind me?

53
00:02:58,460 --> 00:02:59,259
I do not mind you.

54
00:02:59,260 --> 00:03:01,539
You mind me.
Xiao Man, you have changed.

55
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:02,459
I have not.

56
00:03:02,460 --> 00:03:03,620
Then take a sip.

57
00:03:11,140 --> 00:03:12,980
Which way are you turning it?

58
00:03:15,220 --> 00:03:15,980
Drink.

59
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:17,220
All right, then.

60
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:27,139
That is more like it.

61
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:28,580
Listen, Xiao Man.

62
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:29,699
Between brothers,

63
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,980
we should never look down on each other.

64
00:04:11,340 --> 00:04:12,219
Your Majesty.

65
00:04:12,220 --> 00:04:14,620
Have you finished reading the memorials?

66
00:04:15,620 --> 00:04:16,780
Not yet.

67
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,059
Then let us continue.

68
00:04:18,060 --> 00:04:19,180
All right.

69
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:36,980
(Why do I keep staring at him?)

70
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:43,900
Well...

71
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:45,060
Xiao Man.

72
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:46,340
How about today

73
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:48,900
you take the memorials back
and review them yourself?

74
00:04:50,140 --> 00:04:51,540
I want to rest for a while.

75
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,420
All right.

76
00:04:59,260 --> 00:05:00,420
I will leave.

77
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:07,419
(What is wrong with me?)

78
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:09,420
(Why does everything feel strange?)

79
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:14,340
(Why is that?)

80
00:05:14,660 --> 00:05:15,540
Your Majesty.

81
00:05:15,740 --> 00:05:17,100
I am coming in.

82
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:20,260
Come in.

83
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:23,920
I am Duanmu Zhi, heir to the Duke of Ying,

84
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:26,299
formerly a sixth-rank commander
of the Eastern City Garrison,

85
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:27,280
(Duanmu Zhi)
now a fourth-rank blade-bearing guard

86
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:27,859
at Your Majesty's side.

87
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:28,859
I pay my respects

88
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:29,779
to Your Majesty.

89
00:05:29,780 --> 00:05:31,299
All right.

90
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:32,059
Keep it simple.

91
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:34,259
Keep it simple when you speak
to me from now on.

92
00:05:34,260 --> 00:05:35,059
Yes.

93
00:05:35,060 --> 00:05:35,819
Recently,

94
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:37,819
I have investigated
the movements of court officials.

95
00:05:37,820 --> 00:05:39,220
Please have a look, Your Majesty.

96
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:46,260
Not bad.

97
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:47,859
You are quite capable.

98
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:48,939
What else?

99
00:05:48,940 --> 00:05:49,960
I have also verified

100
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:52,680
the background of Your Majesty's
newly appointed scribe eunuch, Xiao Man,

101
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,019
over the past ten years.

102
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:55,260
Please review it, Your Majesty.

103
00:05:57,180 --> 00:05:58,700
Who told you to investigate him?

104
00:06:04,020 --> 00:06:05,219
Why are you not saying anything?

105
00:06:05,220 --> 00:06:06,819
Ever since Xiao Man entered the palace,

106
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:09,860
it feels like Your Majesty treats him
far better than you treat me.

107
00:06:11,020 --> 00:06:12,739
How could you compare yourself to him?

108
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:14,480
Xiao Man is my closest friend
since childhood.

109
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:16,240
I have been waiting
for him to return to the palace.

110
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,300
I...

111
00:06:19,340 --> 00:06:20,460
All right.

112
00:06:21,420 --> 00:06:22,980
I am just a minor official.

113
00:06:23,260 --> 00:06:24,700
He is your dear friend.

114
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:26,980
Then is that still the case now?

115
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:30,619
Shall we dance together again tomorrow?

116
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,780
Woof.

117
00:06:38,420 --> 00:06:40,060
When Xiao Man left back then,

118
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:42,460
he was as clear and pure as water.

119
00:06:42,780 --> 00:06:45,300
Now that he has returned,
he is like an iceberg,

120
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:47,139
with fire hidden deep within.

121
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:48,540
Impossible to fathom.

122
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:51,460
Whenever I try to draw closer to him,

123
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:53,300
I am afraid of getting hurt.

124
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:56,699
I truly cannot imagine

125
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:58,700
how he lived through those ten years.

126
00:07:17,860 --> 00:07:19,379
Why has Your Majesty come here?

127
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:20,500
Xiao Man.

128
00:07:20,780 --> 00:07:22,660
I want you to accompany me for a walk.

129
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:24,580
Your Majesty.

130
00:07:24,660 --> 00:07:26,339
It is already a quarter past midnight.

131
00:07:26,340 --> 00:07:28,220
You still have morning court tomorrow.

132
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:30,300
You are finding fault with me again.

133
00:07:30,740 --> 00:07:32,300
The night is deep and the dew is heavy.

134
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:35,059
Xiao Man is only concerned
for Your Majesty's health.

135
00:07:35,060 --> 00:07:35,819
After all,

136
00:07:35,820 --> 00:07:38,259
the Emperor's well-being
is a matter of the state.

137
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:39,940
Today is my mother's death anniversary.

138
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:45,300
I want you to stay with me.

139
00:08:10,580 --> 00:08:11,699
This is the palace hall

140
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,460
where my mother and I once hid together.

141
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:30,120
My mother was originally
the daughter of a wealthy border family.

142
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:33,780
When she was sixteen,
turmoil broke out along the frontier.

143
00:08:34,460 --> 00:08:36,580
She was saved by General Xiao Congrong.

144
00:08:38,540 --> 00:08:41,060
Later, she was brought back to the palace
and became a palace maid.

145
00:08:41,540 --> 00:08:44,420
When she was eighteen,
she was favored by the Emperor

146
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:46,620
and she secretly gave birth to me.

147
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:50,939
If I had been discovered back then,

148
00:08:50,940 --> 00:08:52,300
I would not have survived.

149
00:08:53,140 --> 00:08:55,340
She took me with her,
hiding from place to place.

150
00:08:57,180 --> 00:09:00,820
It was Eunuch Li and the palace eunuchs
and maids who saved me.

151
00:09:01,620 --> 00:09:03,100
I beg you.

152
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:04,699
Please do not kill my son.

153
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:07,780
He is my only family left in this world.

154
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,820
Do not blame me.

155
00:09:10,060 --> 00:09:13,020
I was only carrying out
the Consort's orders.

156
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:17,140
He is also His Majesty's only bloodline.

157
00:09:17,380 --> 00:09:19,980
I beg you, Eunuch Li.

158
00:09:20,740 --> 00:09:22,740
Make sure the child does not cry.

159
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:25,579
You mother and son will hide here.

160
00:09:25,580 --> 00:09:27,380
I will bring you food.

161
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,259
I will report to the Consort

162
00:09:29,260 --> 00:09:31,380
that the child has
already been dealt with.

163
00:09:31,660 --> 00:09:33,620
As for whether he survives,

164
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:37,020
that will depend
on the young prince's fate.

165
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:40,339
The eunuchs and maids

166
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:42,100
all silently chose not to report it.

167
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:44,860
They even secretly brought us food.

168
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:46,660
And so,

169
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:49,500
my mother and I lived
in an abandoned palace

170
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:51,260
for six years.

171
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:55,780
Later, the Emperor fell gravely ill.

172
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:59,020
Eunuch Li risked his life
to let him know I existed.

173
00:10:00,780 --> 00:10:02,420
You may come out now.

174
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:04,179
I have already reported to His Majesty

175
00:10:04,180 --> 00:10:06,100
the existence of the young prince.

176
00:10:06,140 --> 00:10:08,100
His Majesty wishes to see him.

177
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:10,060
You mother and son

178
00:10:10,580 --> 00:10:13,020
may finally step into the light again.

179
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:15,980
When my origins
were revealed to the world,

180
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:19,500
my mother sensed that her end was near.

181
00:10:22,540 --> 00:10:23,660
My child,

182
00:10:24,380 --> 00:10:27,420
this is as far as I can walk with you.

183
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:28,980
The road ahead,

184
00:10:30,020 --> 00:10:31,620
you must walk it on your own.

185
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:35,100
Remember this.

186
00:10:35,940 --> 00:10:39,660
One must bear
responsibility in this life.

187
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:42,540
And remain true to one's own heart.

188
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:44,180
I

189
00:10:45,540 --> 00:10:47,420
will always be watching over you.

190
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:49,380
I

191
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:52,220
will love you forever.

192
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:58,620
Thank you, Mother.

193
00:11:48,275 --> 00:11:52,195
ظآزI wanted to ask you
the meaning of foreverظآز

194
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:55,720
ظآزIs it longing that never restsظآز

195
00:11:56,375 --> 00:11:59,632
ظآزLove that echoes without endظآز

196
00:12:00,925 --> 00:12:04,520
ظآزOr promises that can't be keptظآز

197
00:12:06,475 --> 00:12:09,895
ظآزAll those vows of forever we madeظآز

198
00:12:10,437 --> 00:12:13,882
ظآزAre sealed away in darkness nowظآز

199
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:18,307
ظآزHow cruelظآز

200
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:22,644
ظآزLove blooms and withersظآز

201
00:12:24,950 --> 00:12:29,032
ظآزThe more I try to forget
the fiercer the love burnsظآز

202
00:12:29,325 --> 00:12:33,420
ظآزThe more I retreat
the sharper it feelsظآز

203
00:12:33,787 --> 00:12:37,099
ظآزHow am I supposed to let goظآز

204
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:41,182
ظآزAnd bring this story to an endظآز

205
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:45,540
Your mother...

206
00:12:48,180 --> 00:12:49,340
She took her own life.

207
00:12:50,860 --> 00:12:52,180
But I know

208
00:12:53,660 --> 00:12:55,220
she did not kill herself.

209
00:12:57,460 --> 00:12:59,020
What about Eunuch Li?

210
00:13:01,540 --> 00:13:02,740
He is dead as well.

211
00:13:03,740 --> 00:13:04,911
He died for me.

212
00:13:04,912 --> 00:13:08,219
ظآزTied to an attachment
that blooms only to fadeظآز

213
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:09,500
I do not even

214
00:13:09,980 --> 00:13:12,660
know what their names were.

215
00:13:14,260 --> 00:13:16,300
I only know my mother's surname was Ji.

216
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:19,059
I once sent many people

217
00:13:19,060 --> 00:13:20,260
to the frontier,

218
00:13:20,580 --> 00:13:22,220
to look for her relatives.

219
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:25,380
But nothing ever came of it.

220
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:31,339
ظآزIf love is meant to fall
more wretched the fiercer its flightظآز

221
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:32,540
But thankfully,

222
00:13:33,380 --> 00:13:35,340
you are here.

223
00:13:55,725 --> 00:13:59,332
ظآزOver countless ages
of this mortal worldظآز

224
00:13:59,725 --> 00:14:03,870
ظآزWhy can I never have my wish fulfilledظآز

225
00:14:03,937 --> 00:14:12,599
ظآزHow absurd that this longing
just won't dieظآز

226
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:17,612
ظآزDo you know, our fingertips
are bound by one stringظآز

227
00:14:17,613 --> 00:14:22,212
ظآزTied to an attachment
that blooms only to fadeظآز

228
00:14:22,213 --> 00:14:23,712
ظآزBy your side onceظآز

229
00:14:23,713 --> 00:14:26,787
ظآزI laughed with the world
wild and freeظآز

230
00:14:26,788 --> 00:14:30,762
ظآزYet now there's no one
to carry the story onظآز

231
00:14:30,763 --> 00:14:35,683
ظآزDo you know you are the one string
woven through my fateظآز

232
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:40,412
ظآزCoiled through the years,
where longing sharpens into pain's lineظآز

233
00:14:40,413 --> 00:14:44,974
ظآزIf love is meant to fall
more wretched the fiercer its flightظآز

234
00:14:44,975 --> 00:14:46,920
ظآزYet I still came to answer your callظآز
